item.description:
Explanation:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
SQL Server has trashed it&#039;s thread that was tied to your SSMS query window and released all resources tied to it (Usually because SQL Server has restarted or someone has killed your process in SQL Activity Monitor).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
When you try to run the first time, nothing will happen because SSMS thinks you&#039;re still connected.  The second time you run the query, this will force a re-connect and open everything back up, allowing you to query away.
